The paper deals with a classic problem in computational biology, specifically the perfect phylogeny problem, which involves constructing an unrooted phylogeny that is compatible with a set of qualitative characters. The paper uses graph theory to characterize when a unique perfect phylogeny exists for a subset of partial characters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
